Rating: 4
The past reviews are pretty much spot on: 1) this recipe is really yummy but don't skimp or skip anything. Individual parts of the recipe will seem ordinary. It really is how it all comes together in one bite. 2) it does take time to make. (Making the tomatillo salsa was what took the longest for me due to the charring step). So make the pickled onions one night; the tomatillo salsa the next; and then the baja cream. Remember also that you need 1-3 hours for the fish to marinate in the buttermilk mixture. Yes, I'd make it again but next time I'll have people over :-)

