Rating: 4
This is my husband's new favorite meal! I agree with so many of the other suggestions so I only have a few to add. To keep the fat down in the baja cream I use equal parts mayo, low fat sour cream and plain, nonfat yogurt. You can't taste a difference. I use coconut milk instead of buttermilk in the fish marinade as it adds a delicious tropical element to the tacos. Finally, I serve chopped cabbage and romaine lettuce for crunch and lightness as otherwise the tacos can be mushy. Oh, and I generally use mahi mahi because it's available so I think just about any mild fish could work.

